<!-- ================= EVACUATION SIMULATION INSIGHTS ================= -->
<section class="simulation-section container">

  <h2>Evacuation Simulation Insights</h2>
  <p class="sim-intro">
    Real-world evacuation simulations help us understand human movement, crowd density,
    congestion points, and alternate escape routes. These insights guide safer building designs
    and effective emergency planning.
  </p>

  <div class="sim-block">
    <img src="/assets/media/main_architecture.jpg" class="sim-img">
    <div class="sim-text">
      <h3>1. Floor Architecture</h3>
      <p>
        Development consist of three different facilities with central courtyard.
        It helps to detect the best possible routes during the time of disaster.
        It helps to find the alternative routes when emergency route is block.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sim-block">
    <img src="/assets/media/floor_architecture.jpg" class="sim-img">
    <div class="sim-text">
      <h3>2. Multi-Floor Evacuation Modeling</h3>
      <p>
        This multi-floor simulation visualizes building-wide evacuation, displaying movement from each floor to the assembly point.
        It highlights how exits must handle synchronized crowd flow from multiple levels during emergencies.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sim-block">
    <img src="/assets/media/Office_evacuation.webp" class="sim-img">
    <div class="sim-text">
      <h3>3. Office Evacuation Visualization</h3>
      <p>
        An office evacuation plan is a formal safety strategy detailing how to safely exit a building during emergencies,
        focusing on clear escape routes, designated assembly points, assigned roles
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sim-block">
    <img src="/assets/media/Fire_evacuation.jpg" class="sim-img">
    <div class="sim-text">
      <h3>4. Fire Evacuation Visualization</h3>
      <p>
       A fire evacuation plan is a safety strategy outlining how to safely exit a building during a fire, featuring clear routes,
       assembly points, roles for fire wardens, and procedures for accounting for everyone, emphasizing using stairs staying low in smoke,
       closing doors, and reporting to a safe meeting spot.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sim-block">
    <img src="/assets/media/archi2.png" class="sim-img">
    <div class="sim-text">
      <h3>5. Staircase Evacuation Flow</h3>
      <p>
        This shows the most critical evacuation paths.  
        This simulation shows how quickly congestion forms on narrow stairs.
        Color gradients help analyze crowd density and walking speed differences across floors.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>



<!-- ================= OFFICE FLOOR DEMO ================= -->

<section class="demo container" id="demo-section">
  <h2>Office Floor Evacuation Demo</h2>
  <p>This example shows how the system reveals evacuation routes and switches to alternate paths when the main exit is blocked.</p>

  <!-- BUTTONS -->
  <button class="toggle-btn" id="routesToggleBtn">Show Evacuation Routes</button>
  <button class="toggle-btn" id="scenarioToggleBtn" style="display:none;">
    Show Blocked Exit Scenario
  </button>

  <div class="demo-wrapper">

    <div class="floor">
      <!-- Rooms -->
      <div class="room room-office1">Office 1</div>
      <div class="room room-office2">Office 2</div>
      <div class="room room-office3">Office 3</div>

      <div class="room room-reception">Reception</div>
      <div class="room room-meeting">Meeting Room</div>
      <div class="room room-pantry">Pantry</div>

      <!-- Corridor -->
      <div class="corridor">Corridor</div>

      <!-- Exits -->
      <div class="exit-main">Main Exit (Stairs)</div>
      <div class="exit-emergency">Emergency Exit</div>

      <!-- Hazard + Blocked icon -->
      <div class="hazard-area hidden" id="hazardArea"></div>
      <div class="blocked-icon hidden" id="blockedIcon">✖</div>

      <!-- PRIMARY ROUTE SEGMENTS -->
      <div class="route primary pr1 hidden"></div>
      <div class="route primary pr2 hidden"></div>
      <div class="route primary pr3 hidden"></div>

      <!-- ALTERNATE ROUTE SEGMENTS -->
      <div class="route alt ar1 hidden"></div>
      <div class="route alt ar2 hidden"></div>
      <div class="route alt ar3 hidden"></div>

      <!-- MOVING PERSON DOT -->
      <div class="person-dot hidden" id="personDot"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="demo-text">
      <h3>How to use this demo</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Click <b>Show Evacuation Routes</b> to reveal the green primary route.</li>
        <li>Then click <b>Show Blocked Exit Scenario</b> to switch to the blue alternate route and show the red hazard.</li>
        <li>Click <b>Show Normal Route</b> to return to the main exit.</li>
        <li>Click <b>Hide Evacuation Routes</b> to clear all paths.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The moving dot represents one person navigating along the currently active evacuation path.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>




